title: Grateful Dead Live at Five Seasons Center on 1984-07-04
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) -> KORG AudioGate 4 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC 24/96; Edited & Mastered with Audacity by Joe Noel: Flac 24/96; Checksum & tags created in xACT; 24 bit to 16 bit with MusicConverter using sox-14-4-2
taper: Robert Bryant patched out of Oade Brothers
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Friend Of The Devil, CC Rider, Cumberland Blues-> Beat It On Down The Line, Row Jimmy, Hell In A Bucket-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Far From Me-> Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Nice audience upgrade ! or something different! Hi GD folks,   this show is one of my favorites from 1984 and should be considered for a legitimate release by GDM/Rhino.  A solid show for our beloved celebration of the USA,  Independence Day !  Yes, and they even played US Blues for the encore!  What else do ya want?  Oh, I know great Good Ol' Grateful Dead !  

I think the 1st set is very strong starting off by Bobby saying " We're gonna start with a drummer's choice " Feel Like A Stranger !  And perhaps , the best solo I've heard from Brent on Friend of the Devil.  A nice midwestern nod to Cumberland Blues and even Hell in a Bucket has a rocking set end slot.  

The second is really amazing,  it's a solid performance with a Pre Drums powerhouse Help > Slip > Franklin's and He's Gone has a nice outro jam and then the cool way to hear "Space > Trucking !  Round it out with a Rascal's Good Lovin, and then top it off with the US Blues encore ! Wow!  

I like this source, it would be cool to hear the master PCM; however,  this analog master may be better as PCM is 14 bit resolution which can be a little grainy sometimes.  I haven't listened to see if the He's Gone Jam is cut but it probably is ... It's evident that the Oade's had good position with a wide stereo field and the mic's seem to be above the audience to limit crowd noise.  I don't download a lot of audience shows but don't overlook this one if you really like this show!
